MC_PRE_ADD_COLLECTIBLE.comment: (CollectibleType Type int Charge boolean FirstTime int Slot int VarData EntityPlayer Player) - Returning a CollectibleType overrides the collectible. You can also return a table of parameters to further modify the collectible given: {Type Charge FirstTime Slot VarData Player}

MC_POST_ADD_COLLECTIBLE.comment: (CollectibleType Type int Charge boolean FirstTime int Slot int VarData EntityPlayer Player),

DEFENSIVE.comment: Dry Baby, Mongo Baby, Cencer, Lil Abaddon

RAYCAST.comment: Similar to ENTITY, and cheaper, but can pass between diagonally adjacent GridEntities

TERTIARY.comment: Offset by 2 of: Pocket Item, Dice Bag Item, Pillcard (Otherwise unused)

QUATERNARY.comment: Offset by Pocket Item and Dice Bag Item and Pillcard (Otherwise unused)

GAME.comment: the actual menu where all the menus are

MOM_KILLS.comment: Stat from the stat screen. Counts kills of Moms heart (Does only count instances where the kill is combined with run "progression". aka in final room and spawning a trapdoor/chest/trophy)

ROCKS_DESTROYED.comment: Includes all rock types including tinted rocks

SUPER_SPECIAL_ROCKS_DESTROYED.comment: Super Special Rocks are Tinted Rock variants with smaller marks and lack of discoloration

POOP_DESTROYED.comment: Includes all poop types. Red poop counts everytime it gets destroyed

PILLS_EATEN.comment: Includes all pills including horse pills

ISAAC_KILLS.comment: How often was the final boss of cathedral killed. (Isaac) (Does only count instances where the kill is combined with run "progression". aka in final room and spawning a trapdoor/chest/trophy)

SATAN_KILLS.comment: How often was the final boss of sheol killed. (Satan) (Does only count instances where the kill is combined with run "progression". aka in final room and spawning a trapdoor/chest/trophy)

SHELLGAMES_PLAYED.comment: How often the shellgame was played

BLUE_BABY_KILLS.comment: How often was the final boss of chest killed. (??? - Blue Baby) (Does only count instances where the kill is combined with run "progression". aka in final room and spawning a trapdoor/chest/trophy)

LAMB_KILLS.comment: How often was the final boss of dark room killed. (The lamb) (Does only count instances where the kill is combined with run "progression". aka in final room and spawning a trapdoor/chest/trophy)

ListValues.comment: Used for elements that use a table as their data source like RadioButtons, Comboboxes, Plots, etc.

Min.comment: min value of a slider input

Max.comment: max value of a slider input

HintText.comment: hint text of a text input, or overlay texts used in plots or progressbars

ColorValues.comment: Color input. 3 values = RGB, 4 values = RGBA

PopupBg.comment: Background of popups, menus, tooltips windows

FrameBg.comment: Background of checkbox, radio button, plot, slider, text input

Header.comment: Header* colors are used for CollapsingHeader, TreeNode, Selectable, MenuItem

ResizeGrip.comment: Resize grip in lower-right and lower-left corners of windows.

TableBorderStrong.comment: Table outer and header borders (prefer using Alpha=1.0 here)

TableBorderLight.comment: Table inner borders (prefer using Alpha=1.0 here)

NavWindowingDimBg.comment: Darken/colorize entire screen behind the CTRL+TAB window list, when active

ModalWindowDimBg.comment: Darken/colorize entire screen behind a modal window, when one is active

GLITCH.comment: Rapidly distorts the spritesheet position. Likely used for glitch items generated by CORRUPTED DATA.

COLOROFFSET_CHAMPION.comment: Used by champion NPCs. If not applied to a champion NPC, it will not render.

STATIC.comment: Used by Dogma (boss, collectible, related effects).

IGNORE_GAME_TIME.comment: If set, animated effects (static, golden) will continue animating even if the game is paused.

ENABLE_LAYER_LIGHTING.comment: Layer names starting with * will become fullbright.

ENABLE_NULL_LAYER_LIGHTING.comment: Null layer names starting with * will emit light.

CHAIN.comment: trigger if previous `ProceduralEffect` is triggered (or dropped by rate).

TRANSFORMATION.comment: This callback is fired immediately before the game transforms Delirium into a boss (this also includes when Delirium returns to its normal form).

POST_TRANSFORMATION.comment: This callback is fired immediately after the game transform Delirium into a boss (this also includes when Delirium returns to its normal form or transforms into the same boss).
